The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, May 17, 2003 				 Medic held
																								New Delhi, May 16: A Deen Dayal Upadhay Hospital doctor was caught accepting a bribe of Rs 10,000 to write a favourable post-mortem report, reports our special correspondent.																								Dr Manoj Nagpal, working in pathology department, demanded the bribe from a person whose cousin had succumbed to injuries in a road accident. He reported the matter to the CBI. 
